<subSubSection id="A9464719DBECA3449B362A62381007DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="097C7A4E9B991E6A42557A59931C7F5A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F2D023AC96229869E7D18BA1446BB639" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
1.6-1.9 mm long (mean = 1.76 mm; n = 5); 2.67-3.17
<normalizedToken id="42A7573B4A17881E9A80D7EE272FDF55" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the entire length of interstriae 2 unarmed by tubercles; posterolateral margin of elytra rounded, unarmed; declivital interstriae flat, interstriae 2 not impressed; and denticles on interstriae 1 and 3 small.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD8C1A4A5A2E0296C719017326804B63" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1DBE9A177B108FA00A6F7377FB6EAFBE" genus="X." lsidName="X. huifenyinae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="huifenyinae">
<emphasis id="894F6AD398B3EB43343A2BDA292AA326" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. huifenyinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is distinguished by the shiny declivity, posterolateral declivity margin rounded and unarmed and smaller denticles on interstriae 1 and 3.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
